(1, 'CFood', '  <div class = \"china\" >\r\n        <div class=\"title2\">\r\n        <h1>Chinese Food</h1>\r\n        <h1>中餐</h1>\r\n        <div class=\"line2\"></div>\r\n    </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"CfoodWrapper\">\r\n  <header class=\"header\"><h1>Resturant</h1></header>\r\n  <div class =\"mainText1\">\r\n        <h2>Laojie Hotpot (老街火锅) </h2>\r\n\r\n    <p>Laojie Hotpot is an ALL you can eat Chinese hotpot specials in Brooklyn, NY. Laojie has a good selection of broth, veggies, meat, and seafood. Also, you can choose to share a big pot with two broths or have your own individual pot. I usually got bone marrow broth and it was very tasteful.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n    <img class =\"divImg1\" src=\"assets/image/laojie.jpg\" alt=\"food\">\r\n\r\n    <img class =\"divImg2\" src=\"assets/image/laojie1.jpg\" alt=\"food\">\r\n\r\n    <img class =\"divImg3\" src=\"assets/image/laojie_bk.jpg\" alt=\"restaurant\">\r\n\r\n\r\n    <div class =\"mainText2\">\r\n    <h3>Laojie Hotpot (老街火锅)</h3>\r\n    <p> Buiness Hours: 1:00PM ~ 2:00AM </p>\r\n    <p> Address: 811 53rd St, Brooklyn, NY 11220</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"CfoodWrapper\">\r\n\r\n  <div class =\"mainText1\">\r\n        <h2>Prince Tea House - 皇室茶园</h2>\r\n    <p>Prince Tea House is a Chinese style dessert shop in Brooklyn, NY. There is a very spacious tea house. People relax and have tea for a while. I always went for milk black tea, and green tea cake. When you getting a tea, there staff give tea in a tea pot, the small candle below the tea pot keeps it warm. </p>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n    <img class =\"divImg1\" src=\"assets/image/r.jpg\" alt=\"food\">\r\n\r\n    <img class =\"divImg2\" src=\"assets/image/tea2.jpg\" alt=\"food\">\r\n\r\n    <img class =\"divImg3\" src=\"assets/image/prince.jpg\" alt=\"restaurant\">\r\n\r\n\r\n    <div class =\"mainText2\">\r\n    <h3>Prince Tea House - 皇室茶园</h3>\r\n    <p> Friday - Saturday: 12:00PM ~ 1:00AM </p>\r\n    <p> Sunday - Thursday: 12:00PM ~ 12:00AM </p>\r\n    <p> Address: 8510 21st Ave, Brooklyn, NY 11214</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<button onclick=\"topFunction()\" id=\"myBtn\" title=\"Go to top\">Top &#8686;</button>\r\n'),
(2, 'JFood', '    <div class = \"japan\" >\r\n        <div class=\"title2\">\r\n        <h1>Japanese Food</h1>\r\n        <h1>日餐</h1>\r\n        <div class=\"line2\"></div>\r\n    </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"JfoodWrapper\">\r\n  <header class=\"header\"><h1>Resturant</h1></header>\r\n  <div class =\"mainText1\">\r\n        <h2>OKONOMI - YUJI Ramen</h2>\r\n    <p>Okonomi is a small Japanese restaurant in Brooklyn, NY. They are the focus on seasonal domestic seafood and Mottainai Philosophy. In the morning, Okonomi serves traditional Japanese set meals for breakfast and lunch. In the evening, Okonomi will become a YUJI Ramen restaurant, it offers an à la carte menu. In all forms, Okonomi strives to embody the Mottainai philosophy of minimizing waste and appreciating what is given. </p>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n    <img class =\"divImg1\" src=\"assets/image/food1_japan.jpg\" alt=\"food\">\r\n\r\n    <img class =\"divImg2\" src=\"assets/image/food2_japan.jpg\" alt=\"food\">\r\n\r\n    <img class =\"divImg3\" src=\"assets/image/japan.png\" alt=\"restaurant\">\r\n\r\n\r\n    <div class =\"mainText2\">\r\n    <h3>OKONOMI // YUJI Ramen</h3>\r\n    <p> Okonomi Breakfast Time: 9:00AM ~ 3:00PM </p>\r\n    <p> Ramen Dinner Time: 6:00PM ~ 11:00PM </p>\r\n    <p> Address: 150 Ainslie St, Brooklyn, NY 11211</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"JfoodWrapper\">\r\n  <div class =\"mainText1\">\r\n        <h2>和参（そして） - WASAN</h2>\r\n    <p>Wasan Brooklyn is a Japanese restaurant in Brooklyn, NY. Wasan\'s motto: \"ingredients are at the heart of cooking. Even the same ingredient can have infinite varieties, depending on where, which season, or under what weather condition they were produced.\" Wasan trying to understand the ingredients, and knows how to make it taste better.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n    <img class =\"divImg1\" src=\"assets/image/wansan2.jpg\" alt=\"food\">\r\n\r\n    <img class =\"divImg2\" src=\"assets/image/wansan1.jpg\" alt=\"food\">\r\n\r\n    <img class =\"divImg3\" src=\"assets/image/wansan.jpg\" alt=\"restaurant\">\r\n\r\n\r\n    <div class =\"mainText2\">\r\n    <h3>和参（そして） - WASAN</h3>\r\n    <p> Business Hour: 11:30AM ~ 10:30PM </p>\r\n    <p> Delivery: 11:30PM ~ 10:00PM </p>\r\n    <p> Address: 440 Bergen St, Brooklyn, New York 11217</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<button onclick=\"topFunction()\" id=\"myBtn\" title=\"Go to top\">Top &#8686;</button>'),
(3, 'Cisland', '  <div class = \"beachImg\" >\r\n        <div class=\"title4\">\r\n        <h1>Coney Island</h1>\r\n        <h1>海邊</h1>\r\n        <div class=\"line2\"></div>\r\n    </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"JfoodWrapper\">\r\n  <header class=\"header\"><h1>Landmarks</h1></header>\r\n  <div class =\"mainText1\">\r\n        <h2>Coney Island beach and Luna park</h2>\r\n        <p>Coney Island is a residential and commercial neighborhood and entertainment area in the southwestern part of the borough of Brooklyn in New York City.Luna Park was an amusement park in Coney Island, Brooklyn, New York that opened in 1903. Built partly on the grounds of Sea Lion Park (1895), it was one of the three original iconic large parks built on Coney Island, the other two being Steeplechase Park (1897) and Dreamland (1904). Luna Park was located on the north side of Surf Avenue on a site between 8th street, 12th street, and Neptune Avenue.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n    <img class =\"divImg1\" src=\"assets/image/coney1.jpg\" alt=\"coney\">\r\n\r\n    <img class =\"divImg2\" src=\"assets/image/coney2.png\" alt=\"coney\">\r\n\r\n    <img class =\"divImg3\" src=\"assets/image/luna.jpg\" alt=\"bridge\">\r\n\r\n\r\n    <div class =\"mainText2\">\r\n    <h3>Luna park</h3>\r\n    <p> Address: Coney Island, Brooklyn, NY </p>\r\n    <p> Saturday - Sunday: 11:00AM - 7:00PM</p>\r\n    <p> Monday - Friday: Closed (Winter)</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<button onclick=\"topFunction()\" id=\"myBtn\" title=\"Go to top\">Top &#8686;</button>'),
(4, 'Bbridge', '<div class = \"bridgeImg\" >\r\n  <div class=\"title2\">\r\n    <h1>Brooklyn Bridge</h1>\r\n    <h1>大橋</h1>\r\n    <div class=\"line2\"></div>\r\n  </div>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"JfoodWrapper\">\r\n  <header class=\"header\"><h1>Landmarks</h1></header>\r\n  <div class =\"mainText1\">\r\n        <h2>Brooklyn Bridge</h2>\r\n    <p>&ensp;&ensp;Brooklyn Bridge is one of the oldest roadway bridges in the U.S. The bridge started construction in 1969 and was complete in 1883. It was the world\'s first steel-wire suspension bridge. Also, it was the first fixed crossing across the East River.I REALLY like across the Brooklyn Bridge from Brooklyn to Manhattan. You can take in the views of Brooklyn, Manhattan, the Statue of Liberty, Sunrise and Sunset. </P>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n    <img class =\"divImg1\" src=\"assets/image/me1.jpg\" alt=\"me\">\r\n\r\n    <img class =\"divImg2\" src=\"assets/image/me.jpg\" alt=\"me\">\r\n\r\n    <img class =\"divImg3\" src=\"assets/image/bridge.jpg\" alt=\"bridge\">\r\n\r\n\r\n    <div class =\"mainText2\">\r\n    <h3>Brooklyn Bridge</h3>\r\n    <p> Address: Brooklyn Bridge, New York, NY 10038</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<button onclick=\"topFunction()\" id=\"myBtn\" title=\"Go to top\">Top &#8686;</button>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n'),
(5, 'Ntransit', '    <div class = \"transitImg\" >\r\n        <div class=\"title1\">\r\n        <h1>Transit Museum</h1>\r\n        <h1>地鐵</h1>\r\n        <div class=\"line1\"></div>\r\n    </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"CfoodWrapper\">\r\n  <header class=\"header\"><h1>Landmarks</h1></header>\r\n  <div class =\"mainText1\">\r\n        <h2>New York Transit Museum</h2>\r\n        <p>&ensp;The New York Transit Museum was founded in 1976, and housed underground in an authentic 1936 subway station in Downtown Brooklyn. It dedicated to telling and preserving the stories of extraordinary engineering feats, workers who labored in the tunnels over 100 years ago, ever-evolving technology, design, and ridership of the system every day. </p>\r\n\r\n        <p>&ensp;When I visited the museum, I can board the vintage cars, sit at the wheel of the city, explore the culture, social and technological history of New York Transit.</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n\r\n    <img class =\"divImg1\" src=\"assets/image/transit5.jpg\" alt=\"train\">\r\n\r\n    <img class =\"divImg2\" src=\"assets/image/transit4.jpg\" alt=\"me\">\r\n\r\n    <img class =\"divImg3\" src=\"assets/image/transit3.jpg\" alt=\"bridge\">\r\n\r\n\r\n    <div class =\"mainText2\">\r\n    <h3>New York Transit Museum</h3>\r\n    <p> Address: 99 Schermerhorn St, Brooklyn, NY 11201</p>\r\n    <p>Monday: Closed</p>\r\n    <p>Saturday - Sunday: 11:00AM - 5:00PM</p>\r\n    <p>Tuesday - Friday: 10:00AM - 4:00pm</p>\r\n  </div>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<button onclick=\"topFunction()\" id=\"myBtn\" title=\"Go to top\">Top &#8686;</button>'),
