(9, 'grading', '    <div class=\"content\">\r\n      <h1>Grade criteria</h1>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n      <h4>Validation</h4>\r\n      <p>1. All pages are validated</p>\r\n      <p>2. All pages display properly in all Browers include IE</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n    <h4>Navigation bar Design</h4>\r\n    <p>1. Labled consistent navigation bar on top of every page.</p>\r\n    <p>2. The navigation bar will have red underline shows where you are.</p>\r\n    <p>3. When you hover the navigation dropdown, there is animation that left and right border will show out.</p>\r\n    <p>4. When browser hits with certain width, the global navigation menu will trun into hamburger bar.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n  <h4>Design Principles</h4>\r\n  <p>1. The page is more consistent than midterm project</p>\r\n  <p>2. Follow the design Principles</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n  <h4>Technology</h4>\r\n  <p><span class = \"cap\">Contact form </span> - The comments will be saved and pulled from database.</p>\r\n  <p><span class = \"cap\">PHP</span> - includes on every page (header and footer)</p>\r\n  <p>If the user <span class = \"cap\">left the textarea blank</span>, the data will not submit and the empty textarea will have <span class = \"cap\">red background.</span> </p>\r\n  <p>JavaScript</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n  <h4>Media Query</h4>\r\n  <p>This Website is display well in <span class = \"cap\">mobile, tablet, and desktop</span>.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n  <h4>JavaScripy</h4>\r\n  <p><span class = \"cap\"> Index Page </span> - use JavaScript to make -Welcome to brooklyn- show up letter by letter.</p>\r\n  <P><span class = \"cap\">Comment Page </span> - use JavaScript to validate if the user left the textbox blank or not. </P>\r\n  <p>In some of long page (like <span class = \"cap\">JapaneseFood page</span>), use javascrpt to let user back to top.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n  <h4>WebSite Design</h4>\r\n  <p><span class = \"cap\">Grid </span> - to make website looks clean 